% rebase("base.tpl")
<div class="row">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h1><i class="fa fa-code-fork"></i>&nbsp;Contribute to Pump19</h1>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="small-11 small-centered columns">
    <p>
      Do you think Pump19 needs a new <dfn>Chem</dfn> (the magic words that power a golem)?
      That can be arranged easily enough.
      Pump19 is built upon <abbr title="Free and open-source software">FOSS</abbr> components and is
      itself released under the <a href="http://opensource.org/licenses/MIT">MIT License</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      All of Pump19's source code is hosted on <a href="https://github.com/"><i class="fa fa-github"></i>&nbsp;GitHub</a>.
      There you can suggest new features, report issues, or even fork and contribute your own functionality.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="small-11 small-centered columns">
    <h2>Repositories</h2>
    <p>
      There exist two distinct source code repositories: one for the chat golem itself and one for
      this website.
    </p>
    <h3>Pump19 <small><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i>&nbsp;Chat Golem</small></h3>
    <ul class="even-2 stack-for-small radius button-group">
      <li>
        <a class="button" href="https://github.com/pyrige/pump19">
          <i class="fa fa-code-fork"></i>&nbsp;Pump19 Source Code
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a class="info button" href="https://github.com/pyrige/pump19/issues">
          <i class="fa fa-bug"></i>&nbsp;Pump19 Issue Tracker
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Pump19.eu <small><i class="fa fa-globe"></i>&nbsp;Website</small></h3>
    <ul class="even-2 stack-for-small radius button-group">
      <li>
        <a class="button" href="https://github.com/pyrige/pump19.eu">
          <i class="fa fa-code-fork"></i>&nbsp;Pump19.eu Source Code
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a class="info button" href="https://github.com/pyrige/pump19.eu/issues">
          <i class="fa fa-bug"></i>&nbsp;Pump19.eu Issue Tracker
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
